'''Karl Wlaschek''' (4 August 1917 – 31 May 2015) was the founder of the Austrian supermarket chain [[Billa (supermarket)|Billa]]. According to the magazine "Trend", Mr. Wlaschek was one of the 5 richest Austrians. In 1996 he sold Billa for 1.1 billion euros.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://derstandard.at/2000016755783/Unternehmer-Karl-Wlaschek-ist-tot|title=Unternehmer Karl Wlaschek ist tot|author=Renate Graber und Claudia Ruff|work=derStandard.at}}</ref>
==Personal life== He lived in Vienna with his fifth wife and had two children.<ref name=Forbes/>
