'''Ola Honningdal Grytten''' (born 30 May 1964) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] economics historian. Born in [[Gothenburg]], [[Sweden]], he graduated with a [[cand.oecon.]] degree from the [[Norwegian School of Economics and Business Administration]]. He also holds a Bachelor in Economic History and a Master in Financial Economics.<ref name=nhh>{{cite web|title=Grytten, Ola Honningdal|url=http://www.nhh.no/Default.aspx?ID=705|publisher=[[Norwegian School of Economics and Business Administration]] (NHH)|accessdate=28 May 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513085911/http://www.nhh.no/Default.aspx?ID=705|archivedate=13 May 2011|df=}}</ref> Grytten has published articles on economics for several Scandinavian publications.<ref name="nhh" />

